FBIS4-13255 "drnes075_r_94004" FBIS-NES-94-075 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 SOUTH ASIA India `Dreaded Militant' Among 4 Killed in Punjab `Dreaded Militant' Among 4 Killed in Punjab BK1904070594 Delhi Doordarshan Television Network in English 1630 GMT 18 Apr 94 BK1904070594 Delhi Doordarshan Television Network English BFN [Text] In Punjab, dreaded militant Avtar Singh, the deputy chief of the Babbar Khalsa, was among four militants killed in an encounter in Punjab. A large quantity of arms and ammunition was recovered from them. Police officials say the security forces cordoned off an area near Sangrur on a tip-off, leading to the encounter. Avtar Singh carried an award of 10 lakh rupees. Police say the gang led by Avtar Singh was responsible for over 100 killings in Punjab. Avtar Singh visited Pakistan on numerous occasions and brought back consignments of weapons to Punjab.
